- To gain access to the next level, you should use the setuid binary in the homedirectory.
  Execute it without arguments to find out how to use it. The password for this level can be found in the usual place (/etc/bandit_pass), after you have used the setuid binary.

setuid (short for "set user identity") is a special file permission that allows a user to execute a program with the privileges of the file's owner rather than the user who launched it.
an executable binary file is a non-human-readable file containing machine code instructions that the CPU can execute directly. To execute you use: ./[file_name]

En este caso recibimos un ejecutable llamado "bandit20-do" al cual ejecutarlo sin argumentos nos dice: "Run a command as another user", o sea corre comandos como el usuario bandit20 con sus permisos
Útil para ver las credenciales de este usuario, el cual es el siguiente nivel.
Por lo tanto escribimos: * ./bandit20-do cat /etc/bandit_pass/bandit20  y recibimos la contraseña para el siguiente nivel.
